cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the problem of allowing external data scientists to explore sensitive datasets while ensuring provable privacy guarantees. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, but the focus on differential privacy and data exploration suggests that cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The paper also presents a novel system for translating accuracy bounds into differentially private algorithms, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The use of adaptive query sequences and the experimental study on real datasets suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also relevant categories.
